&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harrogate &amp; District NHS Foundation Trust &lt;br /&gt;Locum Consultant Gastroenterologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed term contract - 12 month post - Full time - 10 PA&#39;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Locum Consultant Gastroenterologist post at Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant would join the Gastroenterology Department which is comprised of 4 substantive Gastroenterology Consultants and a multi-disciplinary team including two Specialty Doctors, two IBD Specialist Nurses and two Physician Associates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join this incredibly friendly Trust and Department as we look to focus on the recovery of gastroenterology services following the first peak of the coronavirus pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post does not involve any acute medicine on-call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate a consultant of the week model where all routine clinical activities are paused to allow one consultant to support in-patient review and urgent endoscopy every weekday from 9am-5pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Endoscopy Unit is JAG and National Bowel Cancer Screening accredited, and operates out of a new-purpose built unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Complex hepatology is managed by in-reach clinics by a consultant hepatologist and through liaison with the nearby Liver Transplant Centre (Leeds). We run an award-winning specialist coeliac clinic, in addition a visiting consultant delivers specialist hepatology out-patient services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquires please contact Dr Ganesh Sivaji, Clinical Lead or to arrange a visit please contact the Secretary team on 01423 555335.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 22nd November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held on: 30th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Dr Ganesh Sivaji, Consultant Gastroenterologist at ganesh.sivaji@nhs.net or call 01423 555335&lt;/p&gt;
